  "prompt": "How do you pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc?",
  "response": "Pre-selecting a seat when booking a flight with Royal Air Maroc generally involves the following steps:\n\n1. **During Booking:**\n   - **Online Booking:** If you are booking your flight online through the Royal Air Maroc website or app, look for the option to choose your seat during the booking process. There is typically a step where you can view the seat map of the aircraft and select your preferred seat.\n   - **Booking via the Call Center or Travel Agent:** Inform the agent of your seating preference and they can assist you in selecting a seat.\n\n2. **After Booking:**\n   - **Manage My Booking:** If you have already booked your ticket, you can manage your booking by visiting the Royal Air Maroc website and entering your booking reference and last name. This will lead you to your reservation details where you can select or change your seat.\n   - **Call Center:** You can contact the Royal Air Maroc call center and request a seat assignment.\n   - **Mobile App:** Use the Royal Air Maroc mobile app, which may also allow you to choose your seat under the 'Manage Booking' section.\n\n3. **At Check-In:**\n   - **Online Check-In:** Check-in online within 48 hours of departure and select your seat from the available options.\n   - **Airport Check-In:** At the airport, you can request a specific seat during the check-in process.\n\nNote that certain types of seats (like extra legroom seats, front rows, or exit rows) may come with additional charges depending on your fare class and frequent flyer status. Keep an eye on any fee information provided during the seat selection process.\n\nFor detailed and updated information, it\u2019s always best to check directly with Royal Air Maroc or review their official website and customer service guidelines.",
